title: The Murmurs-s/t, White Rabbit EP, Pristine Smut EAC FLAC
description:
This is/was a Boston-based duo of singer/songwriters from the mid 1990s, best known for the vitriolic scorn of 'You Suck' set to a beautiful folk backing. Their style in general is like a more folky and acoustic version of the Indigo Girls, although they can pull the plugs out and do rock and psychedelia-as evidenced by their faithful version of 'White Rabbit'. 

The CD-maxi single contains some stand out tracks. I think there were two other albums released by them before their eventual dissolution-I have them both...but neither are a pale shadow of their first two which are represented here. So take a chance on these relatively small downloads-these are easily worth the bandwidth

I have also included their last and final album-Pristine Smut. This is more produced and less stripped down than the previous two
